Package com.ibm.team.repository.client.util

Provides secondary client-side-only APIs for the Repository component.

See: Description

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    IClientLibraryContext
    Provides special access to the team repository from the client libraries for accessing service interfaces.
    IClientLibraryContext.IServiceRunnable<T>
    The IServiceRunnable interface should be implemented by any class whose instances are intended to be executed as a long-running cancelable operation that makes calls to service methods.
    IEvent
    A description of an event originating from some event source.
    IEventSource
    Represent a generic event source.
    IListener
    Generic event handler interface.
    IPropertyChangeEvent
    A description of a property change that has occurred for some object and originated from some event source.
    ThreadPool.Task
    The signature of tasks accepted by the ThreadPool.
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    ClientLibraryFactory
    The base class of all client library factory implementations.
    DownloadAdapter
    Provides a null implementation of the IDownloadHandler.
    Event
    Base class for events that originate from an event source.
    EventSource
    Implementation of the IEventSource interface.
    FormBasedAuth
    Support for form-based authentication for java.net.* RTC clients.
    FormBasedAuth.JazzSessionCookieHandler
    A cookie handler to deal with Jazz sessionId logins.
    OutputDownloadAdapter
    This adapter class provides default implementations for an output stream download adapter.
    PropertyChangeEvent
    Implementation of the IPropertyChangeEvent interface.
    RepositoryUtil
    Utilities for retrieving information given a specified repository.
    StatisticsUtil
    Utilities for dealing with IStatistics instances.
    StatisticsUtil.MethodNameComparator  
    StatisticsUtil.StatisticsColumn  
    ThreadCheck
    Protection against accidentally invoking long-running operations from threads that must remain responsive.
    ThreadPool
    A pool of threads that cooperate to complete some set of tasks.
    ThreadPool.PoolJob
    The threads responsible for carrying out tasks.
    UploadAdapter
    Provides a null implementation of the IUploadHandler.
